This paper discusses the forensic analysis of cloud storage applications on Android devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of forensics tools and techniques, which could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also touches upon the privacy and security concerns related to cloud storage, which could be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of mobile devices and applications, which could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of data stored in cloud applications, which could be categorized under databases (cs.DB).
